162.4	Umami	Umami	Umami , popularly referred to as savoriness, is one of the five basic tastes together with sweet, sour, bitter, and salty. Umami is a loanword from the Japanese umami ) meaning "pleasant savory taste". This particular writing was chosen by Professor Kikunae Ikeda from umai (うまい) "delicious" and mi (味) "taste". The Chinese characters 旨味 are used for a more general meaning to describe a food as delicious.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Ripe_tomatoes.JPG/220px-Ripe_tomatoes.JPG
